Date: Tue, 31 Mar 2026 02:04:49 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix Apple Watch complication not refreshing on wake

Add complication refresh logic to wake and background task handlers so the watch
complication updates proactively.

Changes:
- Created refreshComplications() helper method to reload all active complications
- Call refreshComplications() when watch app becomes active (on wake)
- Call refreshComplications() when processing WKApplicationRefreshBackgroundTask
- Call refreshComplications() after completing connectivity tasks
- Refactored existing complication refresh code to use the new helper

This ensures complications are refreshed when:
- Watch wakes up and app becomes active
- Data updates are received from the iPhone
- Watch wakes up for background refresh tasks
- After processing WatchConnectivity updates

Previously, complications only refreshed when the user clicked them or when
specific data update notifications fired, causing stale data to be displayed
on wake.

